              "short_description": "UNSW Business School is a prominent business faculty at UNSW Sydney, established in 1955. It comprises seven disciplinary schools and the Australian Graduate School of Management (AGSM), along with six research institutes and various knowledge hubs. The school employs over 400 staff and serves nearly 19,000 full-time students, offering a wide range of programs including undergraduate degrees, specialist master's, MBAs, and executive education.\n\nThe curriculum focuses on practical, career-oriented skills in areas such as accounting, finance, marketing, and emerging fields like business analytics and sustainability. Students benefit from hands-on learning experiences, internships, and strong industry connections, enhancing their employability. The school is globally recognized, holding accreditations from AACSB and EQUIS, and ranks among the top 50 business schools worldwide. Its mission emphasizes transformative learning and partnerships with business, government, and community stakeholders to create sustainable economic and social value.",
